Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text: ONE 22 ONE is located in The Gulch, one of Nashville’s most dynamic neighborhoods, and directly between Downtown and Midtown, providing unparalleled access to an abundance of regional amenities. Beyond the quick and direct commute to the Downtown business and entertainment district, and Midtown’s Music Row, Vanderbilt, and medical districts, the area immediately surrounding the Property is distinguished by being adjacent to the metro’s strongest concentration of destination dining options. The branded “M Street” concepts on McGavock Street and many of the diverse high-quality options within a one-mile radius have won numerous accolades for quality, service, ambiance and value, among other distinctions.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The development offers new premium office space with superior views, efficient floorplates, world-class amenities, ground floor retail, and walkability to area retail and attractions.

Located at the gateway to Downtown Nashville, ONE22ONE will become the most sought-after address in the affluent and highly desired Gulch neighborhood. Sitting at the corner of Broadway and 13th Avenue, ONE22ONE will be the landmark where The Gulch, Midtown, and Downtown Nashville join.

Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
308 Mallory Station Rd is located in Nashville’s popular Cool Springs submarket. This submarket sits in Williamson County, a state leader in both job and population growth. With 13 out of the 25 largest companies in Nashville located in Williamson County, the market’s economy is thriving.
Williamson County boasts a low unemployment rate and a highly educated workforce. That, along with a relatively low cost of living and highly rated school system, further amplifies area’s appeal. With a median household income of $106,045 and a median home value of $472,000, Williamson County has attracted a vibrant community that takes advantage of proximity to top employers, great schools, and plentiful amenities.
